Client spotlight moment 🤍

This client has been committed to an effective hair care journey! Her 1-year journey included consistent appointments every 2 weeks. Her regimen is what I call my “sew in diet”. We start with a sew in installment to last for 6 weeks. After the 6 weeks, she receives a silk press to last her for two weeks, and then followed up with a two-stand twist to last for another 2 weeks. That four-week “rest period” gives her hair a reprieve from the sew-in. 

Once we’re ready to restart the regimen again, then we change the style or side of the part in her natural hair to prevent breakage. 

Within the first 6 months of her process, we had to cut the damaged hair to make room for the healthy new hair growth. Her consistency and diligence has let to much progress; now her hair is trained to hold a strong curl and responds well to being “heat trained” when straightening her hair. 

With the right discipline and regimen, you can also have a similar hair care journey and experience.
